a luncheon with Park Dong-ho.

264
00:22:45,614 --> 00:22:47,657
Before he left for the Blue House,

265
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:49,826
he convened a General Assembly meeting.

266
00:23:01,797 --> 00:23:05,008
These days, it's hard to find
moray fish soup in Seoul.

267
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:07,886
I eat it a couple of times a year
in my hometown.

268
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,846
I get to eat this now, thanks to you.

269
00:23:12,891 --> 00:23:15,769
When you become
the first president from Gangwon-do,

270
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:17,145
please invite me to dinner.

271
00:23:17,229 --> 00:23:19,106
I can get a taste of this soup then.

272
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:29,366
Serving me dessert
before I even finish the meal?

273
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:30,867
Is it that urgent?

274
00:23:32,327 --> 00:23:34,996
Sir, do you remember the promise I made?

275
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:37,541
With all due respect,

276
00:23:38,500 --> 00:23:40,961
may I share
how I would make that happen, sir?

277
00:23:43,171 --> 00:23:45,674
This is what could lead you
to the Blue House.

278
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:51,179
This shows a private equity fund involving
the president's son, Jang Hyeon-su.

279
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:57,185
A few anonymous people invested money
in government-funded projects

280
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:59,771
with information obtained in advance.

281
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:03,483
This is a big corruption case
in which they made a large sum of money.

282
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:06,987
I see.

283
00:24:07,946 --> 00:24:10,282
So that's why I convened
a General Assembly meeting?

284
00:24:11,867 --> 00:24:14,119
And you want me
to instigate an investigation?

285
00:24:14,911 --> 00:24:17,038
You're mocked
as the nine-tailed fox of Yeouido.

286
00:24:17,122 --> 00:24:19,499
This is your chance
to lead a political reform.

287
00:24:37,642 --> 00:24:39,436
Cancel the meeting.

288
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:43,940
Tell everyone
to get on with their schedule

289
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:46,568
and not to worry about
what's happening in Yeouido.

290
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:47,986
Sir!

291
00:24:56,745 --> 00:24:58,246
Assemblyman Park has influence

292
00:24:58,330 --> 00:25:01,666
over half of the Korean Liberal Party,
so if he makes a move--

293
00:25:01,750 --> 00:25:04,419
Assemblyman Park,
a nine-tailed fox of Yeouido.

294
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:08,548
When shit happens,
politicians throw someone under the bus.

295
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:11,635
But he doesn't do that.

296
00:25:12,302 --> 00:25:14,054
He protects his people.

297
00:25:14,596 --> 00:25:16,973
That's why he still has nine tails.

298
00:25:18,558 --> 00:25:20,810
Tails he has kept for 30 years.

299
00:25:20,894 --> 00:25:22,562
He won't cut them today.

300
00:25:23,146 --> 00:25:26,816
If it's a private equity fund involving
the president's son, Jang Hyeon-su,

301
00:25:26,900 --> 00:25:28,693
are the people involved

302
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:30,904
from our side or theirs?

303
00:25:30,987 --> 00:25:32,989
Rotting pus doesn't become your flesh.

304
00:25:33,073 --> 00:25:33,990
You must carve out--

305
00:25:34,074 --> 00:25:36,743
Politicians don't act alone.
There are political forces at work.

306
00:25:37,494 --> 00:25:41,039
If you kick out the flawed ones
and carve out the stinking ones,

307
00:25:41,122 --> 00:25:42,249
our political forces--

308
00:25:42,332 --> 00:25:45,252
If we reveal our flaws and judge them,
people will recognize it.

309
00:25:47,003 --> 00:25:48,213
Do you play poker?

310
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:50,507
I placed my bet

311
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:52,842
to see you play your hand.

312
00:25:52,926 --> 00:25:54,844
Don't ask me to go all in.

313
00:25:57,013 --> 00:25:58,014
Sir.

314
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:00,308
No need for dessert.

315
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:02,310
I'll have another bowl of soup.

316
00:26:04,521 --> 00:26:06,022
Still, he won't give up.

317
00:26:06,648 --> 00:26:07,482
Park Dong-ho is

318
00:26:07,983 --> 00:26:10,777
a hound
that even President Jang couldn't tame.

319
00:26:11,403 --> 00:26:13,113
If that hound bites…

320
00:26:13,613 --> 00:26:15,365
-It can't bite me.
-Sang-un.

321
00:26:22,706 --> 00:26:23,957
You see? It can't.

322
00:26:32,340 --> 00:26:34,050
I still have a quarry to hunt.

323
00:26:35,427 --> 00:26:36,845
Now you need to fetch it.

324
00:26:44,311 --> 00:26:47,897
Even if the truth about the assassination
is revealed tomorrow, we don't flinch

325
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:50,734
until the investigation into
Kang Sang-un and Jeong Su-jin is done.

326
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:56,906
-Hey, Jang-seok.
-Hey, Dong-Ho.

327
00:26:57,407 --> 00:27:00,869
The CIO requested the transfer
of the private equity fund case.

328
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:05,040
Not only did the Prosecutor General
order us to drop the case,

329
00:27:06,166 --> 00:27:07,542
but he also

330
00:27:08,293 --> 00:27:09,961
disbanded the investigation team.

331
00:27:13,715 --> 00:27:15,300
Get the Chief Prosecutor here now!

332
00:27:17,552 --> 00:27:22,265
I was told that coffee is bad for diabetes
and beer is bad for hyperlipidemia…

333
00:27:22,349 --> 00:27:23,642
LEE JUNG-GWON / CHIEF PROSECUTOR

334
00:27:23,725 --> 00:27:26,227
…so I only drink water wherever I go.

335
00:27:30,607 --> 00:27:33,485
Prosecutor Lee has been investigating
this case for a long time.

336
00:27:33,568 --> 00:27:35,737
Send the case back to the prosecution.

337
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:42,577
It is against the law for the Blue House
to intervene in the investigation.

338
00:27:42,661 --> 00:27:44,663
It's within our authority to mediate

339
00:27:44,746 --> 00:27:47,082
when there is conflict
between the agencies.

340
00:27:48,416 --> 00:27:49,959
The Blue House's authority…

341
00:27:51,711 --> 00:27:53,546
I will look for any precedents.

342
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:56,883
I am a little slow,

343
00:27:57,384 --> 00:27:59,678
so it may take a week or two, sir.

344
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:01,304
Mr. Lee!

345
00:28:01,388 --> 00:28:03,348
The higher-ups set the target.

346
00:28:03,431 --> 00:28:05,892
I just pull the trigger, sir.

347
00:28:15,610 --> 00:28:19,197
You can get corporate sponsorship
and support from government agencies.

348
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:22,450
You've dreamed of setting up
a scholarship foundation

349
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:25,495
in your hometown
since you were a lecturer.

350
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:30,250
I will make your dream come true.

351
00:28:33,336 --> 00:28:34,421
Is that your idea?

352
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:38,591
Or Vice Chairman Kang's?

353
00:28:41,219 --> 00:28:42,053
Right.

354
00:28:43,263 --> 00:28:45,974
You two never disagreed on anything.

355
00:28:48,476 --> 00:28:50,854
I only started it to save the president.

356
00:29:00,822 --> 00:29:02,824
Without an anonymous tip,

357
00:29:03,658 --> 00:29:05,994
Assemblyman Seo wouldn't be dead,

358
00:29:06,077 --> 00:29:08,830
there'd be no duress
on the acting president,

359
00:29:09,914 --> 00:29:12,041
and the president
wouldn't have had a mishap.

360
00:29:15,128 --> 00:29:16,421
I found out recently…

361
00:29:19,466 --> 00:29:20,967
who submitted the tip.

362
00:29:26,931 --> 00:29:30,101
I suppose you didn't have
the courage to expose the truth

363
00:29:30,185 --> 00:29:32,437
or the determination to remain silent.

364
00:29:38,485 --> 00:29:40,528
Please resign as Chief of Staff.

365
00:29:46,242 --> 00:29:47,619
In college,

366
00:29:48,661 --> 00:29:50,580
you were very bright.

367
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:56,044
I should teach you something now

368
00:29:56,753 --> 00:29:58,463
that I failed to teach you then.

369
00:30:04,552 --> 00:30:05,762
At your age, ma'am…

370
00:30:08,431 --> 00:30:10,308
it's dangerous to be brave.

371
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,436
-Su-jin--
-Please!

372
00:30:25,949 --> 00:30:27,575
Remain silent.

373
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:44,008
My apologies.

374
00:30:44,717 --> 00:30:46,469
If I wasn't in a rush,

375
00:30:47,178 --> 00:30:48,847
I would've been more polite.

376
00:30:51,641 --> 00:30:52,642
What will happen…

377
00:30:55,895 --> 00:30:57,272
to Acting President Park?

378
00:30:58,356 --> 00:30:59,691
I'm sure he will go down

379
00:31:00,650 --> 00:31:02,902
the same path as the president.

380
00:31:05,071 --> 00:31:07,240
When the first Chief Prosecutor was named,

381
00:31:07,323 --> 00:31:09,951
he was rumored
to be Assemblyman Park's man.

382
00:31:10,618 --> 00:31:12,203
I thought it was just gossip.

383
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:17,625
Jeong-yeon…

384
00:31:21,546 --> 00:31:22,797
we are going with plan B.

385
00:31:47,071 --> 00:31:49,407
The deputy prime minister came to see me.

386
00:31:50,825 --> 00:31:52,702
She promised you your safety

387
00:31:53,453 --> 00:31:54,954
and demanded your resignation.

388
00:32:02,128 --> 00:32:04,672
I'm sure you and I feel the same way.

389
00:32:05,757 --> 00:32:07,425
Are you ready to go all the way?

390
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:16,267
What do I need to do?

391
00:32:20,146 --> 00:32:23,733
Not too long ago,
the president's heart stopped right here.

392
00:32:32,659 --> 00:32:33,493
Tonight,

393
00:32:33,993 --> 00:32:36,704
another heart
will stop beating right here.

394
00:32:48,716 --> 00:32:52,720
We'll celebrate your 80th birthday
and the company's anniversary together.

395
00:32:53,304 --> 00:32:55,139
We'll also invite foreign guests.

396
00:32:55,848 --> 00:32:58,393
You will be pardoned sometime this month.

397
00:32:59,519 --> 00:33:01,020
Of course, I should be.

398
00:33:01,104 --> 00:33:02,730
KANG YEONG-IK / CHAIRMAN OF DAEJIN GROUP

399
00:33:02,814 --> 00:33:04,816
Because as your only father,

400
00:33:04,899 --> 00:33:06,818
only I can hand the company over to you.

401
00:33:07,735 --> 00:33:09,278
But mark my words,

402
00:33:09,362 --> 00:33:13,282
you're not the only son
I can hand my company over to.

403
00:33:14,409 --> 00:33:15,827
I have two more sons.

404
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:24,335
PRIME MINISTER PARK DONG-HO

405
00:33:30,299 --> 00:33:31,759
This is Kang Sang-un.

406
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:33,469
This is Park Dong-ho.

407
00:33:34,137 --> 00:33:36,139
Let's meet at the Blue House tonight.

408
00:34:04,500 --> 00:34:05,334
Let's go.

409
00:34:07,462 --> 00:34:08,296
Chief Kim.

410
00:34:50,296 --> 00:34:53,966
I'd like to sit at a table
with my father before Christmas.

411
00:34:56,135 --> 00:34:58,471
I need to resolve
the issue with the inheritance.

412
00:34:59,097 --> 00:35:02,892
The National Tax Service
is troubling me with inheritance tax.

413
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,521
I'm sure you need to
take control of the company.

414
00:35:08,064 --> 00:35:10,149
If you tell me how much you can pay,

415
00:35:10,733 --> 00:35:11,901
I'll go with that.

416
00:35:18,491 --> 00:35:21,369
"A world
where justice flows like a river."

417
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:27,375
Rivers are full of problems.

418
00:35:27,458 --> 00:35:30,962
Sometimes, it dries up
or overflows from floods.

419
00:35:32,088 --> 00:35:33,965
That's why I'm going to build

420
00:35:34,757 --> 00:35:35,675
a reservoir.

421
00:35:38,845 --> 00:35:42,640
A reservoir that allows as much justice
to flow as the world needs.

422
00:35:44,517 --> 00:35:46,853
I shut the floodgate
when justice flows against me

423
00:35:47,895 --> 00:35:51,399
and open it when it flows in my favor.

424
00:36:09,041 --> 00:36:09,876
Aconitine.

425
00:36:10,418 --> 00:36:13,462
It's extracted from a flower
called wolfsbane.

426
00:36:13,546 --> 00:36:17,425
It's a drug that kills within five minutes
if taken in a lethal dose of 2 mg.

427
00:36:19,218 --> 00:36:20,928
It's diluted, ma'am.

428
00:36:21,012 --> 00:36:24,432
One can survive if their stomach is pumped
within 30 minutes.

429
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:25,850
If we fail

430
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:27,935
today…

431
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:29,729
We will meet in court.

432
00:36:32,815 --> 00:36:35,276
We have been enemies for a long time,

433
00:36:36,485 --> 00:36:38,529
but I hope we'll be friends longer.

434
00:36:45,244 --> 00:36:46,495
Park Dong-ho is…

435
00:36:46,579 --> 00:36:49,332
A hound
that even President Jang couldn't tame.

436
00:36:49,916 --> 00:36:52,877
…a hound
that even President Jang couldn't tame.

437
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:54,212
If that hound bites…

438
00:36:54,795 --> 00:36:56,797
The hound named Park Dong-ho

439
00:36:57,506 --> 00:36:59,008
will bite me.

440
00:37:01,469 --> 00:37:03,095
Jeong Su-jin was right.

441
00:37:04,513 --> 00:37:05,556
Goddammit!

442
00:37:22,698 --> 00:37:23,824
Why didn't you stop

443
00:37:24,325 --> 00:37:25,868
the fight you cannot win?

444
00:37:31,874 --> 00:37:33,459
Why are you holding

445
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:35,962
a drink you cannot sip?

446
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:40,633
Park Dong-ho,

447
00:37:41,509 --> 00:37:43,427
how far were you willing to go?

448
00:37:44,929 --> 00:37:46,597
One step farther than you.

449
00:37:52,687 --> 00:37:53,938
Park Dong-ho!

450
00:38:06,867 --> 00:38:07,785
What a relief.

451
00:38:08,661 --> 00:38:11,831
Whether I die or survive right now,

452
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:14,709
you will not exist…

453
00:38:16,836 --> 00:38:17,795
in my world.

454
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:27,305
Park Dong-ho.

455
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:43,362
The Security Service apprehended
Vice Chairman Kang of Daejin Group

456
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:47,658
for the attempted assassination
of the president at the scene.

457
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:51,954
Two days ago,

458
00:38:52,038 --> 00:38:55,499
the Security Service identified
Vice Chairman Kang as the prime suspect

459
00:38:55,583 --> 00:38:57,918
while investigating the case,

460
00:38:58,002 --> 00:39:01,547
believing that the president's
tragic mishap at the Blue House

461
00:39:01,630 --> 00:39:05,551
was not due to his chronic illness
but by drugs brought in from the outside.

462
00:39:06,802 --> 00:39:10,473
After executing a search and seizure
of Daejin Group's executive office

463
00:39:10,556 --> 00:39:13,267
with the Seoul Central DPO,
we found evidence of a substance

464
00:39:13,351 --> 00:39:16,062
that appears to have been used
in an assassination attempt.

465
00:39:16,645 --> 00:39:19,440
We also secured records of his visit
to the Blue House that night.

466
00:39:19,523 --> 00:39:21,442
VICE CHAIRMAN KANG ARRESTED

467
00:39:21,525 --> 00:39:25,071
We also confirmed
that he hacked into the hospital's server

468
00:39:25,571 --> 00:39:28,949
and stole the president's medical records.

469
00:39:30,242 --> 00:39:32,620
Tonight, to ensure

470
00:39:32,703 --> 00:39:34,622
his own safety,

471
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:37,458
he even tried to assassinate
Acting President Park.

472
00:39:37,541 --> 00:39:39,877
But he was apprehended at the scene.

473
00:39:41,420 --> 00:39:45,508
Acting President Park was rushed
to the Armed Forces Capital Hospital.

474
00:39:46,008 --> 00:39:49,678
The severity of his condition
is yet to be confirmed.

475
00:39:57,728 --> 00:40:00,272
We don't know his condition yet.

476
00:40:00,356 --> 00:40:02,608
Let me know as soon as you find out.

477
00:40:04,318 --> 00:40:05,653
Park Dong-ho set this up.

478
00:40:06,237 --> 00:40:07,738
The public won't be convinced.

479
00:40:07,822 --> 00:40:09,698
Vice Chairman Kang didn't have a motive--

480
00:40:09,782 --> 00:40:14,161
What we have been hiding will surface
as they try to uncover the motive.

481
00:40:16,497 --> 00:40:17,331
We must stop

482
00:40:18,374 --> 00:40:20,459
Park Dong-ho's return to the office…

483
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:25,381
and the Kang Sang-un investigation.

484
00:40:28,342 --> 00:40:29,552
My cell phone!

485
00:40:30,261 --> 00:40:32,972
Where the hell is my cell phone?

486
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:38,018
Well done.

487
00:40:41,313 --> 00:40:42,314
You should go.

488
00:40:43,315 --> 00:40:45,151
Park Dong-ho will show up soon.

489
00:40:46,819 --> 00:40:50,948
Prime Minister Park
will be arrested tomorrow morning.

490
00:40:51,615 --> 00:40:52,825
Why is he coming?

491
00:40:53,701 --> 00:40:55,786
He's determined to come, so I let him.

492
00:40:56,287 --> 00:40:57,746
Also,

493
00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:02,251
I thought I might comfort him
since he is bound to go to prison.

494
00:41:04,712 --> 00:41:06,005
SEO JEONG-YEON

495
00:41:07,339 --> 00:41:08,591
He's having his stomach pumped.

496
00:41:08,674 --> 00:41:11,218
The helicopter got delayed
due to bad weather.

497
00:41:12,386 --> 00:41:14,972
He is in critical condition right now.

498
00:41:27,776 --> 00:41:28,611
Sir.

499
00:41:40,915 --> 00:41:43,334
Has Acting President Park departed?

500
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:50,549
The president is…

501
00:41:57,806 --> 00:41:58,766
awake.

502
00:42:16,158 --> 00:42:19,537
THE WHIRLWIND

